HEADWORD: Sauropoda
<hw>Sau*rop"o*da</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ a lizard + <ets>-poda</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An
extinct order of herbivorous dinosaurs having the feet of a saurian
type, instead of birdlike, as they are in many dinosaurs. It includes
the largest known land animals, belonging to Brontosaurus, Camarasaurus,
and allied genera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sauropsida</ent>⟦br⟧
